    <p class="section-subtitle section-subtitle-center">Prepare 6–8 stories covering these themes — so you can answer any behavioral question without repetition.</p>
    <div class="outcome-grid" style="margin-top:32px;">
      <div class="outcome-card"><strong>Technical or strategic tradeoff</strong><p>A decision between valid options with meaningful consequences for each. Show your reasoning and what you gave up.</p></div>
      <div class="outcome-card"><strong>Execution under pressure</strong><p>High-stakes delivery with a real constraint. Show what you cut, what you protected, how you communicated.</p></div>
      <div class="outcome-card"><strong>Cross-functional conflict</strong><p>A disagreement with a peer or stakeholder. Show how you understood their position and built a better outcome.</p></div>
      <div class="outcome-card"><strong>Failure and recovery</strong><p>Real failure, real stakes, real ownership. Show what changed about how you make that type of decision now.</p></div>
      <div class="outcome-card"><strong>Leadership or influence</strong><p>Moving outcomes without positional authority. Could be upward influence, peer alignment, or developing someone.</p></div>
      <div class="outcome-card"><strong>Measurable business impact</strong><p>Your single best quantified outcome — the highest scope, clearest numbers, most impressive result you have produced.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
